\s The Burden against Nineveh
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 1:1: \xt Jonah 1:1–3 \x* \w  This is the burden  |strong="4853" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.1.1" \w* \w  against Nineveh ,  |strong="5210" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.1.2" \w* \w  the book  |strong="5612" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.1.3" \w* \w  of the vision  |strong="2377" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.1.4" \w* \w  of Nahum  |strong="5151" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.1.5" \w* \w  the Elkoshite :  |strong="512" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.1.6" \w* \v 2 \w  The LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.4" \w* \w  is a jealous  |strong="7072" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.2" \w* \w  and avenging  |strong="5358" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.3" \w* \w  God ;  |strong="410" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.1" \w* \w  the LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.6" \w* \w  is avenging  |strong="5358" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.5" \w* \w  and full  |strong="1167" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.7" \w* \w  of wrath .  |strong="2534" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.8" \w* \w  The LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.10" \w* \w  takes vengeance  |strong="5358" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.9" \w* \w  on His foes  |strong="6862" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.11" \w* \w  and reserves  |strong="5201" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.12" \w* \add wrath\add* \w  for His enemies .  |strong="341" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.2.14" \w* \v 3 \w  The LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.1" \w* \w  is slow  |strong="750" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.2" \w* \w  to anger  |strong="639" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.3" \w* \w  and great  |strong="1419" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.4" \w* \w  in power ;  |strong="3581" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.5" \w* \w  the LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.9" \w* \w  will by no means  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.7" \w* \w  leave the guilty unpunished  |strong="5352" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.6" \w* \w  His path  |strong="1870" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.12" \w* \w  is in the whirlwind  |strong="5492" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.10" \w* \w  and storm ,  |strong="8183" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.11" \w* \w  and clouds  |strong="6051" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.13" \w* \w  are the dust  |strong="80" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.14" \w* \w  beneath His feet .  |strong="7272" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.3.15" \w* \v 4 \w  He rebukes  |strong="1605" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.1" \w* \w  the sea  |strong="3220" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.2" \w* \w  and dries it up ;  |strong="3001" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.3" \w* \w  He makes all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.4" \w* \w  the rivers  |strong="5104" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.5" \w* \w  run dry .  |strong="2717" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.6" \w* \w  Bashan  |strong="1316" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.8" \w* \w  and Carmel  |strong="3760" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.9" \w* \w  wither ,  |strong="535" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.7" \w* \w  and the flower  |strong="6525" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.10" \w* \w  of Lebanon  |strong="3844" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.11" \w* \w  wilts .  |strong="535" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.4.12" \w* \v 5 \w  The mountains  |strong="2022" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.5.1" \w* \w  quake  |strong="7493" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.5.2" \w* \w  before Him ,  |strong="4480" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.5.3" \w* \w  and the hills  |strong="1389" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.5.4" \w* \w  melt away ;  |strong="4127" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.5.5" \w* \w  the earth  |strong="776" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.5.7" \w* \w  trembles  |strong="5375" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.5.6" \w* \w  at His presence —  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.5.8" \w* \w  the world  |strong="8398" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.5.9" \w* \w  and all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.5.10" \w* \w  its dwellers  |strong="3427" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.5.11" \w* \v 6 \w  Who  |strong="4310" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.3" \w* \w  can withstand  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.1" \w* \w  His indignation ?  |strong="2195" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.2" \w* \w  Who  |strong="4310" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.5" \w* \w  can endure  |strong="6965" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.6" \w* \w  His burning anger  |strong="2740" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.7" \w* \w  His wrath  |strong="2534" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.9" \w* \w  is poured out  |strong="5413" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.10" \w* \w  like fire ;  |strong="784" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.11" \w* \w  even rocks  |strong="6697" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.12" \w* \w  are shattered  |strong="5422" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.13" \w* \w  before Him .  |strong="4480" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.6.14" \w* \v 7 \w  The LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.7.2" \w* \w  is good ,  |strong="2896" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.7.1" \w* \w  a stronghold  |strong="4581" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.7.3" \w* \w  in the day  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.7.4" \w* \w  of distress ;  |strong="6869" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.7.5" \w* \w  He cares for  |strong="3045" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.7.6" \w* \w  those who trust  |strong="2620" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.7.7" \w* \w  in Him .  |srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.7.8" \w* \v 8 \w  But with an overwhelming  |strong="5674" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.8.2" \w* \w  flood  |strong="7858" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.8.1" \w* \w  He will make  |strong="6213" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.8.4" \w* \w  an end  |strong="3617" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.8.3" \w*   \add of Nineveh\add* \f + \fr 1.8 \ft Literally "of her place" \f* \w  and pursue  |strong="7291" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.8.7" \w* \w  His enemies  |strong="341" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.8.6" \w* \w  into darkness .  |strong="2822" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.8.8" \w* \v 9 \w  Whatever  |strong="4100" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.9.1" \w* \w  you plot  |strong="2803" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.9.2" \w* \w  against  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.9.3" \w* \w  the LORD ,  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.9.4" \w* \w  He  |strong="1931" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.9.6" \w* \w  will bring  |strong="6213" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.9.7" \w* \w  to an end .  |strong="3617" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.9.5" \w* \w  Affliction  |strong="6869" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.9.11" \w* \w  will not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.9.8" \w* \w  rise up  |strong="6965" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.9.9" \w* \w  a second time .  |strong="6471" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.9.10" \w* \v 10 \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.10.1" \w* \w  they will be entangled  |strong="5440" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.10.4" \w* \w  as with  |strong="5704" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.10.2" \w* \w  thorns  |strong="5518" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.10.3" \w* \w  and consumed  |strong="398" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.10.7" \w* \w  like the drink  |strong="5435" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.10.5" \w* \w  of a drunkard —  |strong="5433" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.10.6" \w* \w  like stubble  |strong="7179" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.10.8" \w* \w  that is fully  |strong="4392" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.10.10" \w* \w  dry .  |strong="3002" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.10.9" \w* \v 11 \w  From you,  |strong="4480" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.11.1" \w* \add O Nineveh\add*  ,  \w  comes forth  |strong="3318" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.11.2" \w* \w  a plotter  |strong="2803" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.11.3" \w* \w  of evil  |strong="7451" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.11.6" \w* \w  against  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.11.4" \w* \w  the LORD ,  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.11.5" \w* \w  a counselor  |strong="3289" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.11.7" \w* \w  of wickedness .  |strong="1100" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.11.8" \w* \v 12 \w  This is what  |strong="3541" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.1" \w* \w  the LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.3" \w* \w  says :  |strong="559" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.2" \w* \w  “ Though  |strong="518" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.4" \w* \w  they are allied  |strong="8003" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.5" \w* \w  and numerous ,  |strong="7227" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.7" \w* \w  yet  |strong="3651" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.8" \w* \w  they will be cut down  |strong="1494" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.9" \w* \w  and pass away .  |strong="5674" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.10" \w* \w  Though I have afflicted you,  |strong="6031" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.11" \w* \add O Judah\add*  ,  \w  I will afflict  |strong="6031" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.13" \w* \w  you no  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.12" \w* \w  longer .  |strong="5750" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.12.14" \w* \v 13 \w  For I will now  |strong="6258" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.13.1" \w* \w  break  |strong="7665" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.13.2" \w* \w  their yoke  |strong="4132" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.13.3" \w* \w  from your neck  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.13.4" \w* \w  and tear away  |strong="5423" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.13.6" \w* \w  your shackles . ”  |strong="4147" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.13.5" \w* \v 14 \w  The LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.3" \w* \w  has issued a command  |strong="6680" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.1" \w* \w  concerning you,  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.2" \w* \add O Nineveh\add*  :  \w  “ There will be no  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.4" \w* \w  descendants  |strong="2232" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.5" \w* \w  to carry on your name  |strong="8034" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.6" \w* \w  I will cut off  |strong="3772" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.10" \w* \w  the carved image  |strong="6459" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.11" \w* \w  and cast idol  |strong="4541" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.12" \w* \w  from the house  |strong="1004" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.8" \w* \w  of your gods ;  |strong="430" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.9" \w* \w  I will prepare  |strong="7760" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.13" \w* \w  your grave ,  |strong="6913" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.14" \w* \w  for  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.15" \w* \w  you are contemptible . ”  |strong="7043" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.14.16" \w* \v 15 \w  Look  |strong="2009" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.1" \w* \w  to  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.2" \w* \w  the mountains —  |strong="2022" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.3" \w* \w  the feet  |strong="7272" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.4" \w* \w  of one who brings good news ,  |strong="1319" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.5" \w* \w  who proclaims  |strong="8085" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.6" \w* \w  peace !  |strong="7965" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.7" \w* \w  Celebrate  |strong="2287" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.8" \w* \w  your feasts ,  |strong="2282" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.10" \w* \w  O Judah ;  |strong="3063" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.9" \w* \w  fulfill  |strong="7999" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.11" \w* \w  your vows .  |strong="5088" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.12" \w* \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.13" \w* \w  the wicked  |strong="1100" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.19" \w* \w  will never  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.14" \w* \w  again  |strong="3254" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.15" \w* \w  march through  |strong="5674" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.17" \w* \w  you ;  |srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.18" \w* \w  they will be utterly  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.20" \w* \w  cut off .  |strong="3772" srcloc="WLC:NAM.1.15.21" \w* 
