.7" \w* \w  on the day  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.3.10" \w* \w  they are prepared ,  |strong="3559" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.3.11" \w* \w  and the spears of cypress  |strong="1265" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.3.12" \w* \w  have been brandished .  |strong="7477" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.3.13" \w* \f + \fr 2.3 \ft Hebrew; alternately, the spears may be of "pine" or "juniper" or "fir"; LXX and Syriac "they are prepared, and the horsemen rush to and fro." \f* \v 4 \w  The chariots  |strong="7393" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.4.3" \w* \w  dash  |strong="1984" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.4.2" \w* \w  through the streets ;  |strong="2351" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.4.1" \w* \w  they rush around  |strong="8264" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.4.4" \w* \w  the plazas ,  |strong="7339" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.4.5" \w* \w  appearing  |strong="4758" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.4.6" \w* \w  like torches ,  |strong="3940" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.4.7" \w* \w  darting about  |strong="7323" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.4.9" \w* \w  like lightning .  |strong="1300" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.4.8" \w* \v 5 \w  He summons  |strong="2142" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.5.1" \w* \w  his nobles ;  |strong="117" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.5.2" \w* \w  they stumble  |strong="3782" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.5.3" \w* \w  as they advance .  |strong="1979" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.5.4" \w* \w  They race  |strong="4116" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.5.5" \w* \w  to its wall ;  |strong="2346" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.5.6" \w* \w  the protective shield  |strong="5526" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.5.8" \w* \w  is set in place .  |strong="3559" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.5.7" \w* \v 6 \w  The river  |strong="5104" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.6.2" \w* \w  gates  |strong="8179" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.6.1" \w* \w  are thrown open  |strong="6605" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.6.3" \w* \w  and the palace  |strong="1964" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.6.4" \w* \w  collapses .  |strong="4127" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.6.5" \w* \v 7 \w  It is decreed that  |strong="5324" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.7.1" \w*   \add the city\add* \w  be exiled  |strong="1540" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2.7.2" \w* \w  and carried away ;  |strong="5927" srcloc="WLC:NAM.2